> ## Hints from an ECS Teacher:
> - When collecting personal inforamtion about students its important to be mindful of the realities in your class. For example, if some students do not always have access to food at home or have an eating disorder it is fine to alter the type of data collected to better suit your students.

## Things to keep in mind

Consider what real world experiences you can use to help your students relate with data and the world around them. What topics do you think might interest your students that you can use as a hook activity?

